This paper deals with the problem of joint spectrum sensing and access in cognitive radio networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also proposes an algorithm for coalition formation, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes simulation results that involve multimedia (cs.MM) data transmission. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI, followed by cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, and cs.MM.
